Active context: the summer internship. This is the live work area.

Scaffold note (generic for now — fill in as the internship ramps up):
- Company / team: TBD
- Tech stack: TBD
- Current project(s): one subfolder per project under Internship-Projects/.
- Each project folder carries its own _context_<project>.md (copy templates/_context_TEMPLATE.md and rename to match the folder).

Project layout convention (follow example-project/):
- Each project lives in Internship-Projects/<project>/ containing: _context_<project>.md (read it first), code/ (working files, indexed), data/ (scratch datasets, I/O), notes/ (project/lab/meeting notes), research/ (background reference material — papers, docs, API/portal write-ups, links).
- Put new working files in that project's code/. Do not invent a different layout.
- If a project maps to a company repo with its own remote, do not nest it here — its _context_<project>.md `repo:` field points to where it lives.

Conventions:
- Day-to-day work logged with templates/daily-log.md; standups with templates/standup-note.md.
- Meetings (1:1s, syncs, reviews) go in meetings/ using templates/meeting-note.md, tagged area/internship.
- When unsure of company-specific tooling or conventions, ask rather than assume.
- Keep the project's _context_<project>.md current: active task, blockers, open questions, next deadline.
